--- @target: std.format
Text formatting utilities for numbers, bytes, and hexadecimal/binary representations.
---

--- @target: BytesStyle
Enumeration for byte display style in human-readable formats.

- `Binary` — displays bytes in powers of 2 (KiB, MiB, GiB).
- `Decimal` — displays bytes in powers of 10 (KB, MB, GB).
---

--- @target: style_binary
Returns the `Binary` bytes style for use with @link bytes.

@return The Binary style enum value.
---

--- @target: style_decimal
Returns the `Decimal` bytes style for use with @link bytes.

@return The Decimal style enum value.
---

--- @target: hex
Formats an integer as a hexadecimal string (base 16).

@param value The integer to format.
@return A text string with the hexadecimal representation.
---

--- @target: bin
Formats an integer as a binary string (base 2).

@param value The integer to format.
@return A text string with the binary representation.
---

--- @target: bytes
Formats a byte count as a human-readable string with specified style and decimal places.

@param value The number of bytes.
@param style The display style (Binary or Decimal). Defaults to Binary.
@param decimals Number of decimal places. Defaults to 1.
@return A formatted string like "1.5 KiB" or "1.5 KB".
---

--- @target: bytes_binary
Formats a byte count as a human-readable string using binary style (powers of 2).

@param value The number of bytes.
@param decimals Number of decimal places. Defaults to 1.
@return A formatted string like "1.5 KiB".
---

--- @target: bytes_decimal
Formats a byte count as a human-readable string using decimal style (powers of 10).

@param value The number of bytes.
@param decimals Number of decimal places. Defaults to 1.
@return A formatted string like "1.5 KB".
---
